metadata.name: Rex Tooth 1
metadata.description: There are 3D scans of adult and juvenile Tyrannosaurus rex teeth excavated in the Hell Creek fromation of North Dakota, USA. The structured light scanning, with detail of +-35 micron, was done with the Faro design edge arm. Tyrannosaurus rex was a carnivorous theropod which existed during the late-Cretaceous period 68-66 million years ago.
